Articles.Content:
So, I've been trying to build a space station just for the heck of it and I had just launched a habitation module into orbit, got everything alined with MechJeb2 and was using the autopilot (hate if you want, but I SUCK at doing these kinds of things) to dock, and when it was suppose to dock and have everything set up so that the module and the bio ring (from the Biodome mod) were together and stuff (I dunno how to explain it) and...lo and behold, it didn't dock, the 2 spaceships collided with each other and that was it, didn't dock, didn't explode (I had all but the pause vessel cheat, because i didn't feel like messing with fuel or anything, when I'm in sandbox mode I tend not to give 2 craps about fuel or anything, I just wanna mess around) and this has happened every time I've tried docking this thing since about last Friday (10-10-14) this is a list of my mods and I'm using KSP 0.24.2 (32 bit)

1. MechJeb2

2. B9 Aerospace 5.2

3. Biodomes

4. Interstellar Space

5. Texture Compression

6. KAS

7. KW Rocketry

8. ScanSAT

my PC stats: Intel Core Duo CPU T6500 @ 2.10 GHz, RAM 4.00 GB (3.87 GB usable), Windows 7 (64 bit OS)

Please help me.
You need to edit your persistant.sfs and Repair the docking port through that, Theres plenty of information on how to do it on google.
